OL,3,CWhat countries are planning to ban
OL,4,Csocial media for under-16s?
OL,6,FAustralia became the first country to
OL,7,Fban social media for under-16s in
OL,8,FDecember, as the government attempted
OL,9,Fto make the internet a "safer place"
OL,10,Ffor young people.
OL,12,FTikTok, Instagram, Facebook, X,
OL,13,FSnapchat, YouTube, Kick, Twitch,
OL,14,FThreads, and Reddit were all impacted
OL,15,Fand had to make changes to their
OL,16,Fplatforms to comply with the new law.
OL,18,FThe rule-change caused huge
OL,19,Fcontroversy, with strong voices both
OL,20,Ffor and against the law. But now,
OL,21,Fother countries are following suit.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
